cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL

The paper deals with a robotics problem of reliable localization using laser in both urban and natural environments. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also involves computer vision techniques for feature extraction and matching, which makes cs.CV (Computer Vision) a likely category as well. The use of Random Forest for matching and estimation falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of shape descriptors and feature extraction, which are common in the field of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques for qualitative and quantitative evaluation, which falls under the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
